  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      During standard colonoscopy a substantial number of colorectal polyps may be missed. Previous
      studies have found a 12-28% of miss rate for all polyps, a 31% for hyperplastic polyps and
      6-27% for adenomas. In this study it is tested whether a retro viewing endoscope can detect
      more colorectal polyps in comparisson to standard forward viewing endoscopy. Further, ppolyps
      detected, mean adenomas per Patient and withdrawal time are recorded.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
